⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 36/120 – Full Outer Join

🎤 Interview Question

Using the same DataFrames,

Write PySpark code to:

1. Perform a Full Outer Join.


2. Display all matching and non-matching rows.




---

✅ Expected Output

dept_id	emp_id	name	department

1	101	John	IT
1	103	Alice	IT
2	102	David	HR
3	104	Bob	NULL
4	NULL	NULL	Finance



---

✅ Recommended Solution

df_emp.join(
    df_dept,
    on="dept_id",
    how="outer"
).show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Difference between Outer Join and Full Outer Join?

Answer

There is no difference.

Both:

how="outer"

and

how="full"

perform a Full Outer Join.


---

Q2. When do we use a Full Outer Join?

Answer

Data reconciliation

Data validation

Comparing two systems

ETL audits



---

Q3. Which join returns the maximum number of rows?

Answer

Full Outer Join, because it includes all matching and non-matching rows from both DataFrames.


